AB  - Using a number of recently completed studies of the scope for factor substitution in industrial processes we estimate the total private benefits of systematic adoption (cost-minimizing) technology as compared with capital-intensive technology. Obstacles to the choice of such technology are examined and presented within a benefit-cost framework. The reasons for some of the current choices of technology are analyzed and policies necessary to alter these are suggested.
